<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><entry xmlns:functx="http://www.functx.com" xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="entry_fæsal" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>fæsal</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>fæsalæ</orth></form><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>подстилка из сухой травы в горской обуви</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>dry grass bedding in mountain shoes</q></cit></sense><cit type="exampleGroup"><cit type="example"><quote>wæd fos k˳yd warzta! — fæsal syn lasta jæ sald ærḱʼījæ</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>как он любил скот! — таскал для них травяную подстилку своего мерзлого арчи</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>how much he loved his cattle! — he dragged the grass bedding of his frozen %sarchi%s for them</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>48</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>fæsalæj basyǧdæǵytæ kodta bæxy</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>сухой травой он обчистил коня</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>he cleaned the horse with dry grass</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>IV 63</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>næwæg fæsal jæ ærḱʼīty bakodta</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>положил свежую подстилку в свои арчи</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>he put fresh bedding in his %sarchi%s</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>III 38</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg type="dialect"><lang/></usg><quote>de ʽrkʼeti fæsalæ din ku næ barævʒæ kænon, wæd mæ baxwærʒænæ</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>если я не приготовлю травяную подстилку к твоим %sарки%s, ты меня съешь</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>if I don’t prepare grass bedding for your %sarki%s, you will eat me</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II 27</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg type="dialect"><lang/></usg><quote>wædi wængæ ba niffæsalæ widæ xwasæ æma næbal bæzzidæ</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>к этому времени трава высыхала („обращалась в %sfæsal%s“) и становилась негодной</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>by this time the grass was dry (‘got turned into %sfæsal%s’) and became unusable</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_SD"/><biblScope>292%l1%l</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><cit type="exampleGroup"><cit type="example"><quote>wæd fos k˳yd warzta! — fæsal syn lasta jæ sald ærḱʼījæ</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>как он любил скот! — таскал для них травяную подстилку своего мерзлого арчи</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>how much he loved his cattle! — he dragged the grass bedding of his frozen %sarchi%s for them</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>48</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>fæsalæj basyǧdæǵytæ kodta bæxy</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>сухой травой он обчистил коня</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>he cleaned the horse with dry grass</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>IV 63</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>næwæg fæsal jæ ærḱʼīty bakodta</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>положил свежую подстилку в свои арчи</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>he put fresh bedding in his %sarchi%s</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>III 38</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg type="dialect"><lang/></usg><quote>de ʽrkʼeti fæsalæ din ku næ barævʒæ kænon, wæd mæ baxwærʒænæ</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>если я не приготовлю травяную подстилку к твоим %sарки%s, ты меня съешь</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>if I don’t prepare grass bedding for your %sarki%s, you will eat me</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II 27</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg type="dialect"><lang/></usg><quote>wædi wængæ ba niffæsalæ widæ xwasæ æma næbal bæzzidæ</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>к этому времени трава высыхала („обращалась в %sfæsal%s“) и становилась негодной</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>by this time the grass was dry (‘got turned into %sfæsal%s’) and became unusable</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_SD"/><biblScope>292%l1%l</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><etym xml:lang="ru">Может быть, из %i*fæd-sal%i, где %ifæd%i ← <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fad"/> ‘нога’ (с ослаблением гласного), а %isal%i из %i*salm%i = <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/><w>слама</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/><w>солома</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lv"><lang/><w>salms</w><gloss><q>солома</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/><w>Halm</w><gloss><q>соломинка</q></gloss></mentioned> и пр. Ср. другое название такой же подстилки в обуви — <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fadxos"/>, где в первой части — <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fad"/> ‘нога’, во второй — <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xos"/> ‘сено’. Что в осетинском существовало в прошлом слово %i*salm%i (или близкое по звучанию), подтверждается косвенно балкарским <mentioned xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><lang/><w>salam</w><gloss><q>трава для подстилки в чувяках</q></gloss></mentioned>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">It may be from %i*fæd-sal%i, where %ifæd%i ← <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fad"/> ‘foot’ (with the vowel weakening), and %isal%i is from %i*salm%i = <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/><w>слама</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/><w>солома</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lv"><lang/><w>salms</w><gloss><q>straw</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/><w>Halm</w><gloss><q>one straw</q></gloss></mentioned> etc. Cf. the other name of the same shoe bedding — <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fadxos"/>, where in the first part there is <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fad"/> ‘foot’, and in the second part there is <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xos"/> ‘hay’. The fact that in Ossetic the word %i*salm%i (or similar in sound) existed in the past is indirectly confirmed by the <mentioned xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><lang/><w>salam</w><gloss><q>grass for shoe bedding</q></gloss></mentioned>.</etym></entry>